xpected and was not much of\na factor.\nBearish sentiment in corn seems\nto increase, with locals selling on\nany bulge and some of the aggres\nsive bears predicting that the May\ndelivery will sell down to GTc or\nGSc some time next month. Others,\nhowever, think prices are close\nenough to the bottom so that a trad\ning attitude is the best one to cul\ntivate. Prices opened %c lower\nthan the previous close.\nOats continued to trail other\n.grains with price changes reflect\ning the variation in prices of the\nother cereals. Opening prices were\nunchanged to %c higher than Mon\nday\u2019s close.\nProvisions opened lower.\nWheat\u2014May unchanged. July\noff %c, September unchanged.\nCorn\u2014May off ^c, July off\nSeptember off %c.\nOats\u2014May up %c, July up\nSeptember unchanged.\nTreasury Statement\nWASHINGTON\u2014The following is a\nstatement of the condition of the United\nStates treasury on March 25:\nIncome to date this year.. $2,966,393,593\nIncome to date last year.. 2,853,512,124\nIncrease 112,881,474\nIncome over outgo this years 392,477,860\nIncome over outgo last year 274,426,053\nIncrease 18,051,607\nBalance general fund today.s 410,902,504\nBalance previous day 409,125,363\nIncrease 1,777,141\nCash Grain\nBarley\nMalting firm and active. Receipt*\nmoderate with some applied on previous\nsales. Good malting demand. Vhoice\nto fancy, 48 to 50 lb. test, quotable at\n84@85c; fair to good, 44 to 47 lb. test,\n77@83c; lightweight, 40 to 43 lb. test.\n73@80c; feed, 63@72c.\nSteady and unchanged with futures.\nReceipts small. Good demand, local and\nshipping. No. 4 yellow quotable 2@4%c\nunder May. No. 4 white at 4@6c under\nMay. No. 4 mixed, 4@6c under May, as\nto moisture and color.\nOats\nEasier with futures to 1c lower for\nlower qualities. Receipts moderate.\nGood demand from shippers and local\nbuyers for bright heavy; poor slow. No.\n3 white quotable 2c over May to la\nunder.\nBye\nSteady to 1c lower with futures. Re\nceipts light. Shipping demand 